      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade E46 M3 in pristine, mint condition. This example is powered by the iconic S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing six individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS high-pressure variable valve timing to achieve a linear, high-revving power band. The mechanical synchronization is flawless; the Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox offers short, tactile throws, feeding power into a speed-sensitive M-Variable limited-slip differential. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, with a verified rear subframe assembly and factory-spec suspension bushings that preserve the original steering rack's communicative feedback. Every seal, gasket, and fluid line is in peak operational state, ensuring the engine operates within its intended thermal and volumetric efficiency ranges. This is a mechanically transparent vehicle for the discerning purist seeking analog perfection.",
